##No one plays in the water during the outbreak, and the swimsuit guys are making Yoga Pants

Reporter: Viann Zhang, Editor: Zhuo Ran Zhou

Many industries are having trouble getting back to work, but Xingcheng swimsuit workers are already in place, only their swimsuits are not being bought.

“

Many industries are having trouble getting back to work, but Xingcheng swimsuit workers are already in place, only their swimsuits are not being bought.

”

Since she resumed work on February 27, she has been "blindly producing" swimsuits at Xingcheng's bedis swimwear factory.

These days, Bedis's workers churn out more than 1,000 swimsuits worth more than 100,000 yuan a day and store them in warehouses, where they can sell at most a dozen or 20 a day.

This time of year, the mid-sized Bedis, like Xingcheng's swimsuit factories large and small, is just getting ready for its first sales peak in years, selling as much as it can make. The machines continue to roar, waiting for the peak season of May Day.

Xingcheng is part of the Huludao province of Liaoning, where the swimwear industry has been in its 1980s since the mid-1990s. Xingcheng now produces a quarter of the world's swimwear, and almost everyone in Xingcheng has at least one swimwear relative. At the end of 2018, there were more than 1,200 swimwear manufacturers in Xingcheng, employing more than 60,000 people, according to the Xingcheng Swimwear Association.

The city of swimwear has come to a sudden halt with an outbreak of new crown pneumonia.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xingcheng beach resort, by Viann Zhang

###Workers were already in place, but no one bought the swimsuits they made

Xingcheng swimwear companies have not been hit by the problems that have plagued many businesses since the outbreak, including delays in the arrival of workers and a lack of a full resumption of work in the supply chain.

The Xingcheng Swimsuit factory is staffed mostly by local workers, and over 30 years of work has left Xingcheng with a relatively complete industrial chain, complete with various accessories factories such as Bra pads, elastic straps and linings. It is not difficult to resume work.

BEDIS bought 5,000 masks for 4 yuan each and sent about 140 workers to work in batches. Each day, 35 workers arrived at the workshop by shuttle bus, each at a distance of 1.5 meters.

The real headache for Xingcheng's swimwear companies was the fact that there were virtually no holidaymakers, bathers or spas across the country during the epidemic, which meant that demand for swimwear across the country dropped to almost zero.

Bedis, a swimwear company that specializes in making all its products domestically, has seen sales plunge nearly 100 percent in the last two months. The workers are in place, but no one buys the swimsuits they make.

Still, workers'wages need to be paid as usual, and Ms. Pan said the factory lost at least 600,000 yuan a month.

Zhao Yang also operates a single within the main swimwear enterprises Xiangyuting, since the outbreak of domestic orders were all cut. "They say it's hard for the restaurant industry, and it's hard for us. The restaurant industry can still do take-out, and we can't do anything because if people don't travel and don't swim, we're basically out of business. "

Before the Spring Festival, Zhao Yang for the future production of more than 100 million yuan of raw materials, goods are now stacked in the warehouse, cash flow began to be tight.

In response to the resumption of production, but also to let the normal operation of the factory, Zhao Yang tried to receive a number of foreign trade processing orders.

Almost all of Xingcheng's swimwear factories specialising in Europe and the US are still receiving orders, with orders falling sharply in Japan and South Korea, which is closely linked to the extent of the outbreak.

But the new orders can hardly bring income to Zhao Yang's factory, because foreign trade orders basically only need to be processed, and Zhao Yang also hired design, typesetting and other higher-paid employees, generally do not have these costs of factories doing foreign trade. So far, the loss of Zhaoyang factory is about 100,000 yuan.

In addition to medium-sized factories, Xingcheng also has a large number of small factories with fewer than 20 employees, which are basically "family workshops" with homes behind them.

The Liu family's small factory, which normally takes orders from China and Japan and South Korea, has been operating for less than a week, with orders falling by less than a tenth of last year's level. Liu said the factory would pay full salaries to workers on an annual basis and give compensation to workers on a piecework basis. Because the factory is small, the losses are relatively small, in the tens of thousands of yuan or so.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xingcheng swimsuit trade city, by Viann Zhang

###A summer of high hopes

The biggest worry for Xingcheng's swimwear community is how long this "half-stop" and "blind production" will last.

"after maybe 10 days and half a month, our factory will face the situation that we don't know what to do, " Liu said. "If we don't have a bill, we may continue to give our employees holidays. "

Pan said the factory could hold out for another two months, and if things don't get better in two months'time, all employees may be given a holiday.

New Crown Disease is likely to subside from late March to mid April 2020 across the country outside of Hubei Province, according to a new study from the Nankai University. Academician Zhong Nanshan recently attended the Guangdong Province Epidemic Prevention and control expert symposium, said that the development of the global epidemic is expected to continue until at least June. In any case, the epidemic does not seem to be getting better any time soon,

In assessing the impact of the NCP epidemic on various sectors, reference is always made to the SARS period. Zhao was the first to bring Xingcheng's wholesale swimwear to Guangzhou, where he was selling swimwear in 2003 and remembers the impact of the epidemic on the industry.

"during the SARS period, I was still looking after the shop. There was business, but it was less. As soon as the government announced the end of SARS, business immediately picked up. As much as the goods came in, they went out. "

Zhao, who has lived through Atypical pneumonia, said the swimsuit industry was much more difficult this year, and he dared not predict when it would get better. "The earliest we can expect is June. "

As the epidemic in Europe and the US intensifies, the only remaining foreign trade orders for Xingcheng's swimwear factories may be in trouble, adding to the woes of the Xingcheng swimwear industry, which has been decimated by domestic sales.

Lau is concerned that the impact on the swimwear industry will last longer. Education authorities in Sichuan, Guangdong and other places have said schools can cut back on summer holidays to compensate for the delayed start of classes, meaning students'summer holidays will be incomplete this year.

Summer vacation has always been a busy season for tourism, but also the swimsuit industry in the most important season of the year. "If the epidemic continues for a long time, we will miss the peak season in July and August, and we will be sad all year. "

Swimwear head brands have suffered limited damage and are more optimistic about the epidemic.

Xingcheng's van der Sar, the top selling swimwear brand on all online platforms in 2019, told interface fashion that sales fell by more than 50% during the worst of the outbreak, but they believe that the second half of the year will usher in swimming fitness and island travel peak period, swimwear category will also rebound into the outbreak period.

Van Der Luyden believes that health has become more important during the outbreak, and he expects a nationwide campaign to culminate once the epidemic is fully under control, with 85 percent of the swimwear category's demand recovering.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photograph: Van Der Luyden

###Sports Yoga products come to the rescue

In fact, most of Xingcheng's small and medium sized swimwear companies were very passive during the epidemic, and they could hardly make up for the losses by moving their locations online, as garment companies or beauty parlors did, because they are not facing the problem of not finding customers, but the problem of not having customers for the time being.

But head brands such as van der Luyden have more room to recalibrate their operations and recoup their losses than small and medium-sized companies.

Van Der Luyden has been in the field of sports yoga since three years ago, introducing products such as Yoga Mats, Yoga Balls and Yoga clothing. He has also adapted some of the swimsuits in his swimsuit collection to wear for sports fitness, Yoga jogging, etc. , but these businesses have been relatively neglected.

During the outbreak, home fitness suddenly became the new Blue Sea, van der Luyden also began to promote its sports yoga products. 3.8 during the shopping festival, sales of Van der Luyden yoga products increased by 465% and sales of yoga mats increased by 668% .

During the outbreak, sports yoga products occupied the TOP of Van der Luyden's store list photo: Van Der Luyden

Although sports yoga products make up less than 20 percent of van der Luyden's total product portfolio, sales of such products can not make up for the loss of swimwear sales, but at least the business has maintained a relatively normal operation, and be prepared for a consumer rebound later.

Sports Yoga products are a lifesaver for swimwear companies. After the outbreak, van der Luyden said he would continue to focus on fashion swimwear, Pan Li, Zhao Yang, Liu Zicen and others said Xingcheng would continue to develop the swimwear industry.

After all, swimwear is a business Xingcheng has been in for more than three decades, and the city has produced a number of second-and third-generation swimwear. And they're all waiting for summer to come.
